This documentation describes the DataStax Enterprise for PCF (Beta) for Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF).  The DataStax Enterprise for PCF enables developers to provision a dedicated DataStax Enterprise (DSE) cluster on-demand to build cloud-scale applications.  
## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

The DataStax Enterprise for PCF (Beta) provides developers the capability to self-service a dedicated DataStax Enterprise (DSE) cluster on-demand.  In our current closed beta period, it exposes three service plans, namely sample-bronze-plan, sample-silver-plan, and sample-gold-plan.  PCF tile administrator can attach different virtual machine types to any of these plans.  Developers will create service plan instances using Cloud Foundry Command Line Interface (cf CLI) and bind them to their apps. 

Creating a DataStax Enterprise for PCF service instance and binding it to an app creates a database connection from an app to a backend dedicated DataStax Enterprise cluster.  This lets developers use the connection to manipulate data residing on the dedicated DataStax Enterprise Cassandra NoSQL database cluster.

## <a id='features'></a>Key Features

DataStax Enterprise for PCF (Beta) includes the following key features:

* Self-provision a DataStax Enterprise (DSE) cluster on-demand with three different service plans.
* Connect PCF apps to a dedicated DataStax Enteprirse (DSE) cluster.
* Decommission a DataStax Enterprise (DSE) cluster.

